### Protocols Summary Table

| Protocol      | Layer          | Purpose                                         | Key Features/Usage                              |
|---------------|----------------|------------------------------------------------|------------------------------------------------|
| TCP           | Transport      | Reliable, connection-oriented data transfer    | Error control, flow control, sequencing         |
| UDP           | Transport      | Fast, connectionless data transfer              | No guarantee of delivery or order                |
| HTTP/HTTPS    | Application    | Web communication                                | Request-response, stateless (cookies for state) |
| SMTP          | Application    | Sending emails                                   | Uses TCP for reliable transfer                   |
| POP3 / IMAP   | Application    | Retrieving emails                                | POP3 downloads email; IMAP syncs across devices |
| DNS           | Application    | Domain name resolution                           | Converts domain names to IP addresses            |
| ARP           | Data Link      | Resolves IP addresses to MAC addresses           | Broadcasts ARP request in LAN                    |
| DHCP          | Application/Data Link | Dynamic IP address assignment               | Assigns IP addresses to devices in a network    |

