### Network Topologies Overview

| Topology      | Description                                   | Advantages                 | Limitations                          |
|---------------|-----------------------------------------------|----------------------------|------------------------------------|
| Bus           | Devices connected to a single backbone        | Simple, easy to implement  | Single point of failure, limited bandwidth |
| Ring          | Devices connected in a circular fashion       | Data flows predictably     | Failure in one link disrupts network |
| Star          | Devices connected to a central hub            | Easy to manage, isolate faults | Hub failure disables entire network |
| Tree          | Combination of bus and star topologies         | Hierarchical, scalable    | Complex, dependent on central nodes |
| Mesh          | Every device connected to every other device  | High redundancy, fault tolerance | Expensive, complex wiring          |

