### Summary of OSI Model Layers and Functions

| Layer         | Function Summary                                                         | Example Protocols/Devices                        |
|---------------|--------------------------------------------------------------------------|-------------------------------------------------|
| Application   | Enables end-user applications to access network services                 | HTTP, FTP, SMTP, DNS                             |
| Presentation  | Data translation, compression, encryption                               | SSL/TLS                                          |
| Session       | Establishes, maintains, terminates sessions                             | NetBIOS, RPC                                     |
| Transport     | End-to-end communication, segmentation, error correction               | TCP, UDP                                         |
| Network       | Logical addressing, routing, packet forwarding                          | IP, ICMP, Routers                                |
| Data Link     | Physical addressing, error detection, frame transmission                | Ethernet, MAC addresses, Switches                 |
| Physical      | Transmission of raw bitstream over physical medium                      | Cables, Radio Frequencies                         |

